'''Veronika Kropotina''' (born January 2, 1991 in [[Moscow]]) is a [[Russia]]n [[figure skater]]. She won three medals, two silvers and one gold, on the [[Junior Grand Prix]], and placed 12th at the 2005 [[World Junior Figure Skating Championships]]. She is coached by [[Elena Buianova]]. She withdrew from the 2005-2006 Junior Grand Prix Final before the event due to illness.

